      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Nightmare start to the quaddie and anything could happen. CATCH A BREAK (1) has a terrible winning strike-rate - 1 from 24 - but most of those were in the previous stable and now with a guy known for turning horses around. Stable debut was adequate for a race like this and strikes the right race to improve again. THEO FIVE (9) is up from the picnics, which generally isn't a great recipe, but that's a stage many here are probably destined for. FASHION FIGHTER (2) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1600m at Warracknabeal, beaten 4.5 lengths into eighth but best is good enough for this. RED STILETTO (7) outrun his price last start at Kilmore, going under 1.6 lengths, and a repeat of them would be more than competitive.",
